Four $5 bills amount to $5 x 4 = $<<5*4=20>>20.
Three $20 bills amount to $20 x 3 = $<<20*3=60>>60.
So Gail's $5 and $20 bills amount to $20 + $60 = $60.
Thus, her $10 bills amount to $100 - $60 = $40.
Therefore, she has $40/$10 = <<40/10=4>>4 $10 bills.
